@heading For the impatient (with only one file download):
@itemize
@item
If you run Windows NT/2000/XP, make sure you are logged in with the
@code{Administrator} rights.
@item
If you have @code{Cygwin} or @code{XEmacs} installed, please read the information below.
@item
Execute the self-extracting installation archive and
@strong{carefully} follow the instructions given there.
Setup will analyze your system, create the corresponding configuration
and give you further tips on the installation process.
(see @uref{http://www.singular.uni-kl.de/WINDOWS/pfwinstall.html})
@item
In case of troubles, see the installed file @code{/etc/INSTALL} or visit
@strong{Singular Forum} at @uref{http://www.singular.uni-kl.de/forum}.
@end itemize

@heading Installation preliminaries

@sc{Singular} is a CYGWIN package on MS Windows: you can install it
with the Cygwin Installer (Net Install):
you will find the packages related to @sc{Singular} under 
@itemize
@item a.Category Math
singular-base, singular-share,
singular-help (optional,recommended),
singular-icons(optional),
singular-surf (optional,recommended)
@item b.Category Editors
emacs or xemacs (optional,needed if you wish to use Singular (Emacs) or ESingular) 
@item c.Category Shells
rxvt (optional,strongly recommended) 
@end itemize

To run @sc{ESingular} (i.e. @sc{Singular} within its Emacs interface) on
MS Windows requires furthermore that the XEmacs editor is installed on
your system.

Complete installation informations for Windows are available from
@display
@uref{http://www.singular.uni-kl.de/WINDOWS/index.html}.
@end display

